  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM - Multi Country Humanitarian Assistance CAP 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over three and a half years have passed since the forced displacement of Rohingya men, women and children from Myanmar into neighbouring Bangladesh. Early leadership exercised by the Government of Bangladesh, with the support of the international community, worked to mitigate and manage the ensuing humanitarian crisis in the southern district of Cox&#x2019;s Bazar. Despite resilience and resolve shown by the refugee community, there exists as of yet no viable solution to the crisis until a safe and voluntary return to Rakhine state is guaranteed. Through this project, IOM is delivering accessible, quality, life-saving assistance to refugees and vulnerable host communities in the Ukhiya and Teknaf Upazilas in Cox&#x2019;s Bazar. This project has four components, which contribute to strengthening the humanitarian access and mobility through the Site Management Engineering Project (SMEP), addressing the urgent protection needs of the Rohingya refugees through strengthening the community-based protection mechanisms, supporting the dedicated position of the Housing, Land and Property (HLP) Coordinator in the Shelter Unit to coordinate the shelter support for the Rohingya refugees, and facilitating the evidence-based response and strong data collection through the IOM Needs and Population Monitoring (NPM) Unit.</narrative>
  </description>
